<ul>
<li>Milind Soman vs Poonam Pandey- Gender Inequality</li></ul>
<h3>LAWS in India</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<table border="1" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="1" style="width:500px">
<tbody>
<tr>
	<td>Aveek Sarkar vs State of WB 1994</td>
	<td>
	<ul>
	<li>SC- "The correct test to determine obscenity would be COMMUNITY STANDARDS TEST (CST) and not HICKLIN Test
	<ul>
	<li>Hicklin Test- Art must be separated from obscenity. (Art &gt; obscenity)</li>
	<li>India follows CST</li></ul></li></ul></td>
</tr>
<tr>
	<td>IPC 1860</td>
	<td>
	<ul>
	<li>Section 294
	<ul>
	<li>Prohibits obscene acts in public place</li>
	<li>Charged on AIB</li>
	<li>Milind Soman</li></ul></li></ul></td>
</tr>
<tr>
	<td>Indecent Representation of Women (Prohibition) Act 1986</td>
	<td>
	<ul>
	<li>Depiction of women, her form or any body part- indecent or derogatory</li></ul></td>
</tr>
<tr>
	<td>IT Act (Amendment) 2008</td>
	<td>
	<ul>
	<li>Section 67(A)- Publication of sexual content will lead to punishment</li>
	<li>Section 67(B)- Prohibits Child Pornography</li></ul></td>
</tr>
<tr>
	<td>Young Person's Harmful Publications Act 1956</td>
	<td>
	<ul>
	<li>If any person advertises or makes known to someone from where harmful publication can be procured</li></ul></td>
</tr>
<tr>
	<td>NHRC/SHRC</td>
	<td>
	<ul>
	<li>Power to protect dignity of women</li></ul></td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
